# The Kaini/Bocuma voice, circuit-corrected: the SH-101's filter is
# the IR3109 — an OTA CASCADE, not a Moog ladder. Our gm-C core
# (circuit 1) is the same circuit family: clean in the passband,
# biting only near cutoff, with the trimmed stable oscillators the
# 101 was known for. One ramp core
# with its converter boards mixed in parallel — the engine's new
# source mixer, phase-locked by construction like the SH-101's.
#   mix: saw dominant, a glint of pulse (the 101 sheet's ~1.5/10),
#   plus the phase-locked sub-square an octave down. One solid
#   voice; no free-running partners, no beating double.
#   Key-followed ladder with a breathing envelope, driven with the
#   saturation stage working. Wow and room live in the song.
